“Thank you @Rahul Shetty for simplifying such a complex AI topic. I now feel ready to step into the world of the Autogen framework in testing. I truly appreciate you publishing this course—I’m really glad I took it.”

This course is a comprehensive introduction to agentic AI and automation workflows, covering key concepts like large language models, AI agents, multi-agent systems, and the MCP protocol. Hands-on projects using the AutoGen framework make learning practical and engaging. It also covers advanced topics such as multi-agent group chats, context engineering, scalable deployment, and human-in-the-loop design. Well-structured and current, it’s ideal for beginners and those seeking to deepen their knowledge in multi-agent AI automation.

Really enjoyed this course! It explains Agentic AI and multi-agent systems in a very simple, easy-to-understand way. The instructor keeps things clear without too much jargon, and the real-world examples make it super practical. Even if you're new to AutoGen or AI automation, you’ll find it easy to follow. The hands-on parts were especially helpful. Great course for anyone curious about using AI agents to automate tasks.
His way of explanation is very lucid and easy to understand the complex scenarios.

This course was a pleasant surprise! I had no prior experience with Agentic AI, but the way the Rahul Shetty broke things down made it easy to grasp. The flow of the lessons felt natural, and the AutoGen demos were really cool. I learned how multiple agents can work together to automate tasks, which was eye-opening. It’s a great starting point if you're exploring AI for the first time and want practical knowledge without getting overwhelmed. Thanks again for this wonderful course and for keeping us up to date with the new technologies.
